Anterior transvertebral transposition of the spinal cord for the relief of paraplegia associated with congenital cervicothoracic kyphoscoliosis. Technical note. The authors describe a technique for the relief of spinal cord compression associated with congenital kyphoscoliosis. A 13-year-old girl with congenital cervicothoracic kyphoscoliosis had undergone in situ fusion spastic paraparesis and bladder disturbance developed postoperatively. Spinal cord detethering and posterolateral decompression temporarily arrested the neurological deterioration